-- J.C. Flowers's Schamis Leaves Symetra Board After Firm Sells Insurer Stake
-- Inyoung Hwang
-- 2010-06-29T20:40:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/j-c-flowers-s-schamis-leaves-symetra-board-after-firm-sells-insurer-stake.html

          
          
             David I. Schamis , a managing
director of New York-based private equity firm J.C. Flowers &
Co., resigned from the board of  Symetra Financial Corp.  as of
June 25.  
 J.C. Flowers sold its stake in Symetra during the Bellevue,
Washington-based insurerâ€™s initial public offering in January,
Symetra said today in a statement distributed by Business Wire.
 Peter S. Burgess , an independent adviser who previously spent 35
years at Arthur Andersen LLP, was appointed to replace him.  
